Cities need food every turn.
The food required in a city depends on the size of the city.
The size of a city is the number of its citizens.
The food required in a city depends on the number of citizens.
The food required in a city depends on the number of settlers.
The food required in a city depends on the city's total food consumption.
The food consumption of citizens is two food points per turn.
The food consumption of settlers depends on the government.
Under anarchy, despotism, monarchy, and communism, the food consumption of settlers one food point per turn.
Under republic and democracy, the food consumption of settlers is two points per turn.